FBIS3-13883 "drnes055dd_94013" FBIS-NES-94-055 Document Type:Daily Report 20 Mar 1994 Palestinian Affairs Hamas Member Captured; 20 Mar Incidents Reported TA2003172594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1600 GMT 20 Mar 94 TA2003172594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Security forces in Gaza have captured a Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] member on the wanted list. Subhi Abu-Khalil is suspected of having killed Palestinians who were believed to have cooperated with Israel. In the village of 'Anabta in Samaria, a Palestinian was wounded when soldiers opened fire on stone-throwers. [passage omitted] An Israeli was lightly wounded in the head when he was hit by a stone while he was driving on the Ben Shemen-Jerusalem road, near the village of Bayt 'Ur al-Tahta. The Tel Aviv Magistrates Court has sentenced Gaza resident Masrah Barbah to life in prison, after finding him guilty in the murder of Moshe Becker, a citrus grower from Rehovot, two months ago. Another suspect in the murder, Hani Abu-Sittah, denied the charges and is currently being tried.
